FeedPackage.Description:
Inspired by Dapper, SprocMapper is an easy to use and light-weight object-relational mapper specifically designed for stored procedures.
Some key differences to Dapper: - Supports caching. - If a select column in stored procedure can't be mapped, an exception will be thrown (this feature can be turned off but is recommended) - Type validation - Keep your stored procedures readable. Using aliases on select columns is supported.
See https://github.com/gtaylor44/SprocMapper for examples.

FeedPackage.Description:
Enable your applications to become high-throughput, cross-platform, full-duplex, stand-alone WebSocket servers and/or clients optimized for pushing real-time data to large number of connections. PowerWebSockets features lightweight JSON messaging, push-to-all, burst messaging, streaming API, per-message compression, TLS with X.509 and username/password authentication, advanced keep-alive and more.
This package pulls in all the assemblies required for creating servers and clients running on .NET Framework (server-side & client-side), .NET Compact Framework (server-side & client-side), Xamarin.iOS (server-side & client-side), Xamarin.Android (server-side & client-side), Windows Phone (client-side), Silverlight (client-side) and Mono (server-side & client-side).
FeedPackage.Summary: PowerWebSockets is a performance-oriented implementation of WebSocket, the most important new protocol standardized by the IETF that is intended specifically for bidirectional communication between all types of clients and servers.
FeedPackage.Tags: Noemax PowerWebSockets websocket full-duplex bi-directional real-time self-hosted asynchronous communication server client streaming compression JSON messaging
FeedPackage.Title: Noemax.WebSockets

FeedPackage.Description: NoFake is a Unit Test helper library that provides an opportunity to create a real test environment. For example, if test method requires some folder to have a list of specific files NoFake will handle it: files will be created at the beginning of test method and removed in the end, when all stuff is done.
